article.headline: Tennessee St. 75, SE Missouri 72
article.story: NASHVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- Larry Turner had a career-high 22 points and eight rebounds for Tennessee State to hold off Southeast Missouri 75-72 Thursday night. Tennessee State (3-4, 1-0 Ohio Valley Conference) took a 46-35 lead at the half on 53.6 percent shooting from the field. Southeast Missouri (3-6, 1-1) took advantage of its bench in the second, scoring 29 points to the Tigers' 15 and outscoring them 37-29 in the half. The Tigers went cold from the arc in the second, missing all six 3-point attempts. Ladarious Weaver added 13 points and Ervin Reiley had 12 for the Tigers. Marcus Rhodes came off the bench to lead the Redhawks with 17 points, including 8-of-10 from the line, followed by Brandon Foust with 14 points and a team-high seven rebounds, David Johnson with 13 points and Terrick Willoughby with 10. Southeast Missouri's Roderick Pearson and Michael Rembert fouled out.
